You are given a space separated list of numbers.
Your task is to print a reversed NumPy array with the element type float.

Sample Input

1 2 3 4 -8 -10
Sample Output

[-10.  -8.   4.   3.   2.   1.]


SOLUTION:
import numpy

def arrays(arr):
    # complete this function
    # use numpy.array
    a = numpy.array(arr[::-1], float)               //To store the array as the reverse of the list (negative indexing)
    return a
